   <concept id="i6_302-5"
            ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2"
            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">6.302-5</ph> Authorized or required
by statute.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d384e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d391e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                   Authority.</p>
               <ol id="d384e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e27" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                         Citations: <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2304(c)(5)</xref> or <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.3304(a)(5)</xref>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e42" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                         Full and open competition need
not be provided for when–</p>
                     <ol id="d384e48" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d391e52" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                               A statute expressly authorizes
or requires that the acquisition be made through another agency
or from a specified source; or</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d391e61" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                               The agency’s need is for a brand
name commercial item for authorized resale.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d391e74" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Application</i>.
This authority may be used when statutes, such as the following,
expressly authorize or require that acquisition be made from a specified
source or through another agency:</p>
               <ol id="d384e83" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e87" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                         Federal Prison
Industries (UNICOR) <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">18 U.S.C. 4124</xref> 
                        <ph class="- topic/ph ">(see <xref href="FAR-i1117091.dita#i1117091"
                                 base="i1117091"
                                 outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                                 class="- topic/xref ">subpart  8.6</xref>).</ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e105" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                         Qualified
nonprofit agencies for the blind or other severely disabled <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.chapter 85,</xref> Committee
for Purchase From People Who Are Blind or Severely Disabled (see <xref href="FAR-i1116916.dita#i1116916"
                              base="i1116916"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  8.7</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e120" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                         Government
Printing and Binding <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">44 U.S.C. 501-504</xref>,
1121 <ph class="- topic/ph ">(see <xref href="FAR-i1116866.dita#i1116866"
                                 base="i1116866"
                                 outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                                 class="- topic/xref ">subpart  8.8</xref>).</ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e138" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                         Sole source
awards under the 8(a) Program (15 U.S.C. 637), but see <xref href="FAR-i1119735.dita#i1119735"
                              base="i1119735"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">6.303</xref> for requirements
for justification and approval of sole-source 8(a) awards over $22
million. (See subpart <xref href="FAR-i1099848.dita#i1099848"
                              base="i1099848"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.8</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e153" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(5)</ph>
                         Sole source
awards under the HUBZone Act of 1997-<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">15 U.S.C.657a</xref> (see <xref href="FAR-i1099639.dita#i1099639"
                              base="i1099639"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.1306</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e169" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(6)</ph>
                         Sole source
awards under the Veterans Benefits Act of 2003 (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">15 U.S.C.657f</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li id="i1119663" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e181" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(7)</ph>
                         Sole
source awards under the WOSB Program–<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref "> 15 U.S.C. 637(m)</xref> (see <xref href="FAR-i1099284.dita#i1099284"
                              base="i1099284"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.1506</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d391e198" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                   Limitations.</p>
               <ol id="d384e198" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e208" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                         This
authority shall not be used when a provision of law requires an
agency to award a new contract to a specified non-Federal Government
entity unless the provision of law specifically—</p>
                     <ol id="d384e208" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d391e218" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                               Identifies
the entity involved;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d391e227" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                               Refers
to <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2304(k)</xref> for
armed services acquisitions or <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 3105</xref> for
civilian agency acquisitions; and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d391e242" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph>
                               States
that award to that entity shall be made in contravention of the
merit-based selection procedures in <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2304(k)</xref> or <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 3105</xref>, as
appropriate. However, this limitation does not apply–</p>
                           <ol id="d384e248" class="- topic/ol ">
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p id="d391e258" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(A)</ph>
                                     When
the work provided for in the contract is a continuation of the work
performed by the specified entity under a preceding contract; or</p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p id="d391e267" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(B)</ph>
                                     To any
contract requiring the National Academy of Sciences to investigate,
examine, or experiment upon any subject of science or art of significance
to an executive agency and to report on those matters to the Congress or
any agency of the Federal Government.</p>
                              </li>
                           </ol>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e280" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                         Contracts
awarded using this authority shall be supported by the written justifications
and approvals described in <xref href="FAR-i1119735.dita#i1119735"
                              base="i1119735"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">6.303</xref> and <xref href="FAR-i1119818.dita#i1119818"
                              base="i1119818"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">6.304</xref>, except for–</p>
                     <ol id="d384e286" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d391e296" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                               Contracts
awarded under <ph class="- topic/ph ">(a)(2)(ii) or
(b)(2) of this section;</ph>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d391e308" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                               Contracts
awarded under <ph class="- topic/ph ">(a)(2)(i) of this
section</ph> when the statute expressly requires that the procurement
be made from a specified source. (Justification and approval requirements
apply when the statute authorizes, but does not require, that the
procurement be made from a specified source); or</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d391e320" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph>
                               Contracts
less than or equal to $22 million awarded under <ph class="- topic/ph ">(b)(4) of this section.</ph>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e334" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                         The authority
in <ph class="- topic/ph ">(a)(2)(ii) of this section</ph> may
be used only for purchases of brand-name commercial items for resale
through commissaries or other similar facilities. Ordinarily, these
purchases will involve articles desired or preferred by customers
of the selling activities (but see <xref href="FAR-i1119438.dita#i1119438"
                              base="i1119438"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">6.301</xref>(d)).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
